aa(lp35
VSo, I went to design school,
p36
aVand it was the early '90s when I finished.
p37
aVAnd I saw something extraordinary happening in Silicon Valley,
p38
aVso I wanted to be there,
p39
aVand I saw that the computer was coming into our homes,
p40
aVthat it had to change in order to be with us in our homes.
p41
aVAnd so I got myself a job and I was working for a consultancy,
p42
aVand we would get in to these meetings,
p43
aVand these managers would come in,
p44
aVand they would say,
p45
aV"Well, what we're going to do here is really important, you know."
p46
aVAnd they would give the projects code names, you know,
p47
aVmostly from "Star Wars," actually: things like C3PO, Yoda, Luke.
p48
aVSo, in anticipation, I would be this young designer
p49
aVin the back of the room, and I would raise my hand,
p50
aVand I would ask questions.
p51
aVI mean, in retrospect, probably stupid questions,
p52
aVbut things like, "What's this Caps Lock key for?"
p53
aVor "What's this Num Lock key for?" You know, that thing?
p54
aV"You know, do people really use it?
p55
aVDo they need it? Do they want it in their homes?"
p56
aV(Laughter)
